### 2.2 Configurable Latency for Performance Tests

**Extended Interceptor:**

```dart
class ConfigurableLatencyInterceptor extends Interceptor {
  final Map<String, int> endpointLatencies;

  ConfigurableLatencyInterceptor(this.endpointLatencies);

  @override
  void onRequest(RequestOptions options, RequestInterceptorHandler handler) async {
    final path = options.path;

    // Different latency per endpoint
    if (path.contains('/inspections/sync')) {
      await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: endpointLatencies['/sync'] ?? 100));
    } else if (path.contains('/photos/upload')) {
      await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: endpointLatencies['/photos'] ?? 500));
    }

    handler.next(options);
  }
}
```

**Usage:**

```dart
test('Simulate slow photo upload', () async {
  final mockDio = Dio();
  mockDio.interceptors.add(
    ConfigurableLatencyInterceptor({
      '/sync': 50,    // Fast metadata sync
      '/photos': 2000, // Slow photo upload (2s per photo)
    }),
  );

  // Test adaptive behavior
  final syncEngine = SyncEngine(dio: mockDio);
  await syncEngine.sync();
});
```

